Define the parameters in the HTML template, corresponding to the
templateParameters config of html-webpack-plugin. You can use the config as an
object or a function.

If it is an object, it will be merged with the default parameters. For example:

export default {
  html: {
    templateParameters: {
      title: 'My App',
    },
  },
};


If it is a function, the default parameters will be passed in, and you can
return an object to override the default parameters. For example:

export default {
  html: {
    templateParameters: defaultParameters => {
      console.log(defaultParameters.compilation);
      console.log(defaultParameters.title);
      return {
        title: 'My App',
      };
    },
  },
};



