#

This section describes the configuration of the Runtime plugin.


Configuration#


runtime#

 * Type: Object

The runtime is configured as follows:

Base#

Configure in modern.config.ts:

modern.config.ts



export default defineConfig({
  runtime: {
    state: true,
    router: true,
  },
});


DefineConfig#

Configure use defineConfig API:

INFO
When there is a function in the runtime configuration, it can only be configured
in this way.
src/App.tsx



const App = () => {
  /** */
};

defineConfig(App, {
  router: {
    supportHtml5History: false,
  },
});

export default App;


INFO
Using runtime configuration, you can solve the problem that runtime plugin
configuration needs to be at runtime to get specific content.

Runtime plugin runtime configuration and configuration directly in
modern.config.ts are merged by default, and runtime configuration takes
precedence.

WARNING
defineConfig can only define the specific configuration content of the Runtime
plugin. To confirm whether to enable the plugin, it needs to be determined
through the configuration in modernConfig in package.json or modern.config.ts.


runtimeByEntries#

 * Type: Object

Introduction#

Add the runtime configuration according to the entry. The option attribute is
consistent with the runtime. The specified value will be replaced and merged
with the content of the runtime attribute.

modern.config.ts



export default defineConfig({
  runtime: {
    state: false,
  },
  runtimeByEntries: {
    entry1: {
      state: true, // { state: true }
    },
    entry2: {
      // { state: false, router: true }
      router: true,
    },
  },
});

