Add Error Status#

When the micro-frontend sub-application fails to load or render, the loading
component will receive the error parameter (if there is no error, the error is
null).

function Loading({ error }) {
  if (error) {
    return 
Error msg {error?.message};
  } else {
    return 
Loading...;
  }
}


Avoid Loading Flash Back#

Sometimes the display time of the loading component may be less than 200ms, and
the loading component will flash back at this time. Many user studies have
proved that the loading flash back situation will cause the user to perceive
that the loading content takes longer than the actual time.

When loading is less than 200ms, if the content is not displayed, the user will
think it is faster.

Therefore, the loading component also provides the pastDelay parameter, which
will only be true when it exceeds the set delay display. You can set the delay
duration through the delay parameter.

function Loading({ error, pastDelay }) {
  if (error) {
    return 
Error! {error?.message};
  } else if (pastDelay) {
    return 
Loading...;
  } else {
    return null;
  }
}


The default value of delay is 200ms, you can set the delay display time through
delay in loadable.


