Add Timeout State#

Sometimes because of the network, the micro-front-end sub-application fails to
load, resulting in the loading state being displayed all the time, which is very
bad for users, because they don't know the right response to get a specific
response, whether they need to refresh the page, by Increasing the timeout state
can solve this problem well.

The loading component will get the timeOut parameter when timeout, when the
micro frontend application loads timeout, it will get the timeOut property value
of true.

function Loading({ error, timeOut, pastDelay }) {
  if (error) {
    return 
Error! {error?.message};
  } else if (timeOut) {
    return 
Loading timed out, please refresh the page... ;
  } else if (pastDelay) {
    return 
Loading...;
  } else {
    return null;
  }
}


